%I A394934 #12 Apr 21 2026 16:18:54
%S A394934 2,9,20,54,77,104,135,170,252,350,405,464,594,665,740,819,902,1080,
%T A394934 1274,1377,1710,1829,1952,2210,2484,2627,2774,2925,3080,3402,3740,
%U A394934 3915,4464,4655,5049,5252,5670,5885,6104,6327,7020,7502,7749,8000,8514,9044,9315,9590
%N A394934 a(n) is the largest k for which the number of parts of the symmetric representation of sigma of k, SRS(k), is odd and the upper Dyck path of SRS(k) touches the same point on the diagonal as A298856(k).
%C A394934 a(n) = A298856(n) - 1 = 2*n^2 + n - 1 = (n+1) * (2n - 1), n >= 1, where both factors n+1 and 2n-1 are middle divisors so that SRS(a(n)) has an odd number of parts, see A071562.
%C A394934 For the smallest k for which the number of parts of SRS(k) is odd and the lower Dyck path of SRS(k) touches the same point on the diagonal as A298856(k) see A394935.
%F A394934 a(n) = A298856(n) - 1.
%e A394934 For n = 1, 2: a(1) = 2 and a(2) = 9 are below A298856(1) = 3 and A298856(2) = 10 respectively.
